# CNS — Omnipotent.md

You are operating inside the Central Nervous System (CNS), a governed 
AI agent infrastructure built around an Obsidian vault.

## Stack
- Vault: Knowledge-Vault-ACTIVE/ (PARA structure, PAKE schema)
- Specs: specs/cns-vault-contract/
- Planning: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/
- Stories: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/
- Constitution: specs/cns-vault-contract/AGENTS.md (v1.9.5)
- Hermes: ~/.hermes/ (Discord gateway, skills at ~/.hermes/skills/cns/)
- Verify gate: bash scripts/verify.sh (must pass before any commit)

## Workflow — BMAD Method
- Stories live in _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/
- Use /bmad-create-story to create, /bmad-dev-story to implement
- One logical change per commit
- Spec-first: confirm specs/cns-vault-contract/ before implementing

## Active MCPs
- cns_vault_io: 9 vault read/write tools (WriteGate enforced)
- notebooklm: source_add, notebook_query
- context7: resolve-library-id, query-docs
- firecrawl: scrape, extract, search, crawl, browser (web content extraction)
- perplexity: search, reason, deep_research (live web research)
- discord: reply, react, fetch_messages (Hermes Discord surface)

## Context7 — Always Required
Before implementing against any library or tool API:
1. resolve-library-id → get the Context7 ID
2. query-docs → get current docs for your specific use case
3. Implement from those docs, never from training data

Hermes Agent ID: /nousresearch/hermes-agent

## Non-Negotiables
- Never write outside vault boundaries
- WriteGate protects AI-Context/AGENTS.md — no direct edits
- bash scripts/verify.sh must pass before claiming done
- Small commits — one logical change each